Ulnar dimelia is a congenital deformity where the thumb is absent, the ulna is duplicated, and there are seven or eight fingers in the hand. Have you ever heard of mirror hand syndrome? Ulnar dimelia or mirror hand syndrome is a rare congenital anomaly of the upper limb characterized by absence of radius, duplication of ulna and symmetric polydactyly (seven or eight fingers and lack of thumb).
